<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-02-01T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-02-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="771" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50/1135: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Chargé in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Matthews</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-02-01T22:00:00-04:00">February 1,
                                1943—10 p.m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>677. Your 583 January 21, midnight, and 584 January 21, 1 p.m.<note n="22" xml:id="d771fn22">Latter not printed.</note> The Department sees no
                        objection to procedure along the lines set forth in the British Government’s
                        reply to the Brazilian Ambassador’s communication of December 30.</p>
                    <p>The Department would consider it desirable to continue the “stalling off”
                        process with relation to Argentina’s interest in the matter.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>